content: This app is terrible. The questions don't make any sense and the answers are totally illogical. There is no way I would ever reccomend this app for anybody. This was a terrible waste of money and I wish I could get my money back. DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY! To IFSTA, Please reference IFSTA Fire and Emergency Services Instructor 8th edition, chapter 12, page 317, lines 20-28 with a emphasis on bullet point #2. When constructing a test eliminate lengthy, complex, or unclear sentences.

The app is helpful, but by itself will not ensure you pass. It is a useful study aid and the provided page numbers and study deck are great. However, I need to ding the app for not being super user friendly. The biggest issue being that it will not save your progress on a quiz. Multiple times I've been going through a 500 plus question quiz and I'll accidentally hit the back button and completely lose my place, or the app will go idle and I have to start over again. It's very frustrating.

Passed my test thanks to this app. The questions are not identical to the test, but they get you thinking about the material. The wording of the questions is poor, but so was the case on the actual certification test. This is just the nature of the subject material rather than a flaw in this app.
Not even close to what is on the exam. Biggest waste of $9.99. Thieves!
Questions are lazily written. They leave out key words, which makes the question confusing and inaccurate. Not the studying tool I expected it to be.

This app did not help with testing what so ever. I bought this in hopes of getting a better understanding of the material but all I found was poorly worded questions that had little to no relation to the state test. Lucky I read the book and was able to pass. My advice? Skip this garbage app and just read the book.
Very well done app. I love the ability the options to study missed questions and change the number of questions and multiple choice attempts.
Used if for FI 2 & 3. Questions written in a similar way with similar content to the actual exam. It is a tool to assist with test prep, not the only tool to use.
I was terrified of the presentation portion of this course.. But this app helped me thru the exam portion.
This app is great as with all state tests there are many versions with reading the book and confirming that knowledge on here my confidence is going way up.
Aced every pretest on this app and there might have been  three total questions on the actual test.  Don't waste your money
replyContent: In order to achieve maximum academic integrity all of our quiz, test, and Exam Prep Plus questions are written independently and are not recycled. While the questions may cover similar content they will always be different.  Our questions are designed to test your knowledge, not to give you an advanced look at your certification exam.
